article.description: Allen's dunk puts Sacred Heart past Colgate 71-70
article.headline: Allen's dunk puts Sacred Heart past Colgate 71-70
article.linkText: Allen's dunk puts Sacred Heart past Colgate 71-70
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Jordan Allen's dunk off an inbounds pass with six seconds to go lifted Sacred Heart over Colgate 71-70 on Wednesday night. Ethan Jacobs made two free throws to put Colgate up 70-67 with 1:06 left to play. Allen made a layup to cut the difference to one point and Jacobs missed a 3-point attempt to put the ball back in the Pioneers' hands with 34 seconds left. Sacred Heart (3-3) called a timeout and Allen dunked on Phil Gaetano's inbounds pass for the difference. Gaetano had eight assists. The Raiders led by as many as five points with 2:16 to play, but four-straight points from Sacred Heart's Cane Broome kept the Pioneers alive. Broome finished with 21 points and Allen had 14. Jacobs scored 20 points for Colgate (1-6), Austin Tillotson added 15 and Luke Roh grabbed 11 rebounds.
